OL,3,CRSPCA warns the number of people
OL,4,Cabandoning pets is rising
OL,6,FThe Salford and Manchester RSPCA
OL,7,Fbranch took in ten animals between
OL,8,FChristmas and New Year. Emma Sweeney
OL,9,Fvisited them to find out why animal
OL,10,Fabandonment is on the rise.
OL,12,FKittens Elena and Katerina were left
OL,13,Fon a doorstep on Christmas day. But
OL,14,Ftheir story is not unique, 2025 has
OL,15,Fbeen one of the most challenging on
OL,16,Frecord for the RSPCA.
OL,18,FReports of animals being abandoned
OL,19,Fhave sky-rocketed.
